            <abstract><p>Thanks for gift of book and letter of recollections. Gratified by Lady Smith's support of her husband's late conduct [Thomas Milner Gibson (1806-1884), politician] and its contrast from the ill nature and persecution they have received from those that previously professed friendship. Invites Smith to visit.</p><p>[Note in red ink on verso of second folio giving brief biographical details of the letter sender. Letter dated 14 September but no year given]</p></abstract>
